Run
#yum install httpd


Important files / dir for web services

/etc/httpd/conf - main configuration directory
/etc/httpd/conf.d - customization directory
/etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf - main configuration file
/var/www/html -htmp directory called “Document Root”- where the server domian resides
/var/log/httpd - httpd directory -keeps track of all the activity of website (the log) all the log for apache is here


from the /etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf   file 
#<VirtualHost *:80>
#    ServerAdmin webmaster@dummy-host.example.com
#    DocumentRoot /www/docs/dummy-host.example.com
#    ServerName dummy-host.example.com
#    ErrorLog logs/dummy-host.example.com-error_log
#    CustomLog logs/dummy-host.example.com-access_log common
#</VirtualHost>
